# Architecture

## Structure
- Domain-oriented: `features/dom`, `features/classification`, `features/insights`, `features/sentry`
- `shared/types` for project-level types, `shared/utils` for small reusable helpers
- `components/` for pure UI only

## Boundaries
- `features/dom`: DOM reading, extraction, normalization only. No classification. No React.
- `features/classification`: Pure rule-based functions. No DOM access. No React.
- `features/insights`: Summary, hypothesis, priority, useful-frame. Pure functions. No DOM. No React.
- `features/sentry`: Orchestration between extraction, classification, and rendering.
- `components/`: Pure UI. No business logic.

## Code Style
- No `any` — use `unknown` + narrowing when needed
- Pure functions wherever possible
- No business logic inside React components
- Files should stay under ~200 lines
- No premature generic abstractions — build concretely first
- No dead files or placeholder architecture without implementation
